# Molecular Dynamics Simulation Protocol

This document describes the molecular dynamics (MD) simulation protocol used to study PSMA–conjugate complexes.

All simulations were performed using GROMACS 2024.4 with GPU acceleration.

---

## 1. System Preparation

### Protein

- Structure: PSMA extracellular domain (PDB ID: 5O5R)
- Force field: AMBER99SB-ILDN
- Water model: TIP3P
- Protonation state assigned at pH 7.4
- Crystallographic waters removed prior to topology generation
- Catalytic Zn2+ ions retained

Topology generation:
gmx pdb2gmx -f PSMA.pdb -o protein.gro -p protein.top -water tip3p -ignh

---

### Ligands

- Ligand parameters generated using ACPYPE
- Underlying force field: GAFF2
- Partial charges derived from quantum mechanical calculations (CHELPG)
- prmtop/inpcrd files converted to GROMACS format

acpype -p ligand.prmtop -x ligand.inpcrd -o gmx

Protein and ligand coordinate files were merged to construct each PSMA–conjugate complex.

---

## 2. Simulation Box and Solvation

- Box type: cubic
- Minimum solute–box distance: 1.0 nm
- Water model: TIP3P (spc216.gro)
- System neutralized
- Ionic strength: 0.15 M NaCl

gmx editconf -f complex.gro -o complex_box.gro -c -d 1.0 -bt cubic  
gmx solvate -cp complex_box.gro -cs spc216.gro -o complex_solv.gro -p complex.top  
gmx genion -neutral -conc 0.15  

---

## 3. Energy Minimization

- Integrator: steepest descent
- Maximum steps: 100,000
- Convergence criterion: 500 kJ/mol/nm
- Position restraints applied to protein and ligand

Nonbonded interactions:
- PME electrostatics
- Real-space cutoff: 1.4 nm
- van der Waals cutoff: 1.4 nm
- Verlet cutoff scheme
- Dispersion correction: EnerPres

---

## 4. Equilibration

### NVT Equilibration

- Duration: 500 ps
- Integrator: stochastic dynamics (Langevin-type)
- Time step: 1 fs
- Temperature: 310.15 K
- Thermostat: V-rescale
- Position restraints applied to protein and ligand

### NPT Equilibration

- Duration: 500 ps
- Integrator: stochastic dynamics
- Time step: 1 fs
- Temperature: 310.15 K
- Pressure: 1 bar
- Barostat: Parrinello–Rahman (isotropic)
- Position restraints applied to protein only

Electrostatics and cutoffs identical to production settings.

---

## 5. Production Simulations

- Duration: 400 ns per replica
- Replicas: 3 independent simulations per system
- Time step: 2 fs
- Integrator: stochastic dynamics
- Temperature: 310.15 K
- Pressure: 1 bar
- Thermostat: V-rescale
- Barostat: Parrinello–Rahman (isotropic)
- PME electrostatics
- Real-space cutoff: 1.4 nm
- van der Waals cutoff: 1.4 nm
- LINCS constraints on hydrogen bonds
- No position restraints

Trajectory frames saved every 10 ps.

Independent replicas were initiated using distinct random seeds to ensure statistical independence.

---

## 6. Analysis

Analyses were performed using MDAnalysis and custom Python scripts:

- Backbone RMSD
- Residue-level RMSF
- Radius of gyration
- Protein–ligand contact analysis
- Minimum-distance profiling

All analysis scripts are available in the repository.

---

End of MD protocol.
